LIMITED USE AGREEMENT
THIS LIMITED USE AGREEMENT ("Agreement") is entered into this 18th, day of August, 2021 (the "Effective Date"), by and between Norris Electric Cooperative ("Grantee") and Illinois Power Generating Company, an Illinois corporation ("Owner").
Recitals WHEREAS, Grantee is a party to that certain Power Supply Agreement between Illinois Power Marketing Company, an affiliate of Owner ("IPM") and Grantee dated and effective as of July 21, 2014, as amended by that certain First Amendment dated and effective April 6, 2016, that certain Second Amendment dated and effective December 2, 2019, and that certain Third Amendment of even date herewith (the "Third Amendment") (as amended, the "Power Supply Agreement"); WHEREAS, pursuant to the Power Supply Agreement, IPM sells at wholesale the power generated at the Newton Power Station 6725 North 500th Street, Newton, Illinois 62448 Jasper County (the "Property"), which is owned by Owner; WHEREAS, the Newton Power Station is interconnected to the bulk transmission system through the Newton Unit 1 345 kV Gen-Tie line with Point of Interconnection at the bus connection point between Ameren air break switches W-3488 and E-3489 and certain other interconnection facilities, located on the Property (the "Equipment"); WHEREAS, pursuant to the Third Amendment, IPM and Grantee have agreed to certain power supply terms and conditions to serve the Data Center (as defined therein) to be located and operated on the Property; and WHEREAS, in connection with the Data Center, Grantee wishes to use the Equipment for the limited purpose of providing energy to the Data Center during those periods in which the Newton Power Station is not operating, and Owner wishes to grant such limited use, as more particularly set forth herein. NOW THEREFORE, for One Dollar ($1.00), the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, Grantee and Owner agree as follows: Agreement for Limited Use of the Equipment 1. Limited Use. Upon the effective date, Grantee shall have the limited, non-exclusive right to use the Equipment solely to facilitate the transfer of up to 140 MW of power to the Data Center during certain periods of time within the term of the Power Supply Agreement (the "Limited Use"). Grantee shall only use the Equipment for the Limited Use during such periods of time when Grantee is providing to the Data Center power that is not generated by the Newton Power Station (the "Use Periods"). Grantee shall have no right to use the Equipment outside of the designated Use Periods. During Use Periods, Grantee shall only be permitted to use the Equipment to the extent that the Equipment is in-service and Grantee's use does not interfere with Owner's use and enjoyment of the Property, Equipment or Owner's operations or activities on the Property, whether now existing or planned or permitted for the future. Grantee shall comply with Owner's requests and directions related to the use or operation of the Equipment. 2. Term and Termination. The term of the Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue until the earlier of (i) the permanent retirement of the Newton Power Plant; (ii) May 31, 2026; or (iii) termination by Owner or Grantee. Owner or Grantee may terminate this Agreement upon 30 days' notice to the other party.
3. Maintenance of Equipment. Owner shall own, operate, and maintain the Equipment during the term of the Agreement.
4. Replacement of Equipment. Grantee shall use its best efforts to minimize damage to the Property or the Equipment due to Grantee's Limited Use and must promptly notify Owner of any damages to the Property or the Equipment resulting from the same. Grantee shall be solely responsible for the costs of any damage to the Property or Equipment resulting from Grantee's Limited Use or other actions of Grantee.
5. Compliance with Laws. Grantee agrees that, in the exercise of all of its rights and privileges hereunder, Grantee shall conduct all such actions in compliance with all applicable laws, rules and regulations of the State of Illinois, United States of America, and all state, federal and local governmental agencies and authorities having regulatory authority over such actions and/or the Property.
6. Owner's On-Site Terms and Conditions. Grantee shall comply with Owner's terms and conditions related to the safe and secure use of the Equipment.
7. Indemnity. GRANTEE SHALL, INDEMNIFY, DEFEND, SAVE, PROTECT AND HOLD OWNER AND ITS OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, AGENTS, REPRESENTATIVES, AFFILIATES, SUBSIDIARIES, SUCCESSORS AND ASSIGNS HARMLESS FROM AND AGAINST ANY AND ALL CLAIMS, LIABILITIES, LOSSES, DAMAGES, DEMANDS, LAWSUITS, CAUSES OF ACTION, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO CLAIMS FOR PERSONAL INJURIES, DEATH, DAMAGES TO PROPERTY, AND ALL OTHER CLAIMS OR DEMANDS AND COSTS AND EXPENSES (INCLUDING ATTORNEY'S FEES, COSTS OF LITIGATION AND/OR INVESTIGATION OR OTHER COSTS ASSOCIATED THEREWITH) ARISING OUT OF, RESULTING FROM, CAUSED BY, OR IN ANY WAY RELATED TO (A) THE ENTRY OR PRESENCE UPON THE PROPERTY BY GRANTEE ITS AGENTS, EMPLOYEES, SERVANTS, AUTHORIZED CONTRACTORS, OR GUESTS, (B) GRANTEE'S LIMITED USE OF THE EQUIPMENT, (C) ANY BREACH OF THIS AGREEMENT, AND/OR (D) THE NEGLIGENCE OR MISCONDUCT OF GRANTEE, SAVE AND EXCEPT TO THE EXTENT ANY SUCH LIABILITY RESULTS FROM THE GROSS NEGLIGENCE OR INTENTIONAL MISCONDUCT OF OWNER.
8. Limitation of Liability. NEITHER OWNER NOR GRANTEE SHALL BE LIABLE TO THE OTHER FOR ANY SPECIAL, PUNITIVE, EXEMPLARY, INDIRECT, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES, OR LOSSES OR DAMAGES FOR LOST REVENUE OR LOST PROFITS, WHETHER FORESEEABLE OR NOT, ARISING OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT.
9. Liens. Nothing contained in this Agreement shall empower Grantee to do any act which can, shall or may encumber the Property, Equipment, or the title of Owner therein. Grantee has no authority or power under this Agreement to cause any lien, charge or encumbrance of any kind whatsoever, whether created by act of Grantee, operation of law or otherwise, to attach to or be placed upon the Property, Equipment, or Owner's title or interest therein. Grantee covenants and agrees not to suffer or permit any lien of mechanics or materialmen or others to be placed against the Property, Equipment, or any part thereof with respect to work or services claimed to have been performed for or materials claimed to have been furnished to Grantee for the Property, Equipment, or any part thereof.
10. Notices. Any notice to be given hereunder shall be in writing and hand delivered or sent by certified United States mail, return receipt requested, addressed to the parties at the addresses set out below. Notices or other communications hand delivered shall be deemed received on the date delivered. Notices or other communications sent by certified mail shall be deemed received when delivered or when delivery is refused, as evidenced by the postal service return receipt. Any changes in the respective addresses to which such notices are sent shall be communicated by the method provided herein to be effective upon receipt thereof. Notices shall be addressed to the parties as follows:
To Owner: To Grantee:
Illinois Power Generating Company Norris Electric Cooperative Legal Department Attn: Tamera Phillips - General Manager 6555 Sierra Drive 8643 N. State Highway 130 Irving, TX 75039 Newton, IL 62448
11. Miscellaneous.
Binding Effect. This Agreement shall be binding upon Grantee, Owner, and their respective successors and permitted assigns. Grantee shall not assign this Agreement or any of its rights or responsibilities arising hereunder to any individual or entity without first having obtained the written approval of Owner. Any assignment that does not comply with the prior sentence shall be void ab initio. Governing Law, Venue. This Agreement is being executed and delivered, and is intended to be performed, in the State of Illinois, County of Jasper. The validity, construction, enforcement, and interpretation of this Agreement shall be governed by and be construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Illinois, without regard to conflict of laws, rules or principles which might result in application of the law of another jurisdiction. Each party submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of said courts and waives the right to change venue. Entirety and Amendments. This Agreement (including all exhibits) embodies the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior agreements and understandings, if any, relating to the matters addressed herein. This Agreement may be amended or supplemented only by an instrument in writing executed by both parties. Illegal Provisions. If any provision of this Agreement is held to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable under present or future laws effective during the term of this Agreement, the legality, validity and enforceability of the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall not be affected thereby, and in lieu of each such illegal, invalid or unenforceable provision there shall be added automatically as a part of this Agreement a provision as close in meaning to such illegal, invalid or unenforceable provision as may be possible and be legal, valid and enforceable.
Non-Waiver. Any party's failure or delay in protesting or taking legal and/or equitable action upon the other party's breach is not to be considered as being a waiver of that party's cause of action for any subsequent breach.
Relationship Between the Parties. Nothing contained herein shall be deemed to create an association, joint venture, partnership or principal/agent relationship between the parties.
FERC Approval. The parties acknowledge that the effectiveness of this Agreement will be contingent on the acceptance of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
No Third Party Beneficiaries. This Agreement is entered into for the sole benefit of the parties, and except as specifically provided herein, no other person shall be a direct or indirect beneficiary of, or shall have any direct or indirect cause of action or claim in connection with, this Agreement.
Disputes. Any dispute under this Agreement between Grantee and Owner must, at the request of any Party, be referred to a senior representative of each of the Parties for resolution on an informal basis as promptly as practicable. The negotiation and any documents exchanged in connection with the negotiation shall be confidential and considered statements made in compromise negotiations within the meaning of the Federal Rule of Evidence 408 and any applicable state law, evidentiary rules or doctrines. In the event the Parties are unable to satisfactorily resolve their dispute within thirty (30) calendar days of such referral to the senior representatives or such other period as the Parties may mutually agree, subject to any extensions of time as may be mutually agreed upon in writing, either Party may pursue such remedies as may be available to it under applicable Law or in equity in order to resolve such dispute.
